tr.td: MALAISE AND FATIGUE (Primary Dx);VACCINE FOR STREP PNEUMONIAE;SCREENING MAL NEOP-RECTUM;ESSENTIAL HYPERTENSION;HYPOTHYROIDISM;HYPERCHOLESTEROLEMIA

td.paragraph: Diagnosed 1/25/95 by elevation of TSH after presentation for general exam with persistent fatigue as primary symptom. Synthroid started at that time. Family history negative for thyroid disease.

Diagnosed age 54. Initially treated with sodium restriction, diet, exercise. Diuretics started ~1988, taken sporadically since that time. Patient admits to poor compliance with med regimen. No history to suggest end organ damage or coronary artery disease. Cardiovascular risk factors include 20 pk yr hx of smoking and hypercholesterolemia.
GERD, diagnosed by EGD. Symptoms well controlled with intermittent prn use of H2 blockers.
Started smoking age 16, smoking 1 - 1.5 ppd. Has made several half-hearted attempts to quit but has never been successful for longer than a few days. Only smoker in the family.
